2. Refaya AK, Kumar N, Raj D, et al. Whole-genome sequencing of a _Mycobacterium orygis_ strain isolated from cattle in Chennai, India. Microbiol Resour Announc. 2019; 8(40): e01080-19. Published 2019 Oct 3. https://doi.org/ 10.1128/MRA.01080-19.
3. Thapa J, Nakajima C, Maharjan B, Poudell A, Suzuki Y. Molecular characterization of _Mycobacterium orygis_ isolates from wild animals of Nepal. Jpn J Vet Res 2015; 63(3): 151-8. https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26563034/
4. WHO, FAO, OIE. Roadmap for zoonotic tuberculosis; https://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/handle/10665/259229/9789241513043-eng.pdf;jsessionid=84F540C176F6E55E6690319BC5C5C47B.
5. Marcos LA, Spitzer ED, Mahapatra R, et al. _Mycobacterium orygis_ lymphadenitis in New York, USA. Emerg Infect Dis. 2017; 23(10): 1749-1751. doi:10.3201/eid2310.170490; https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5621560/
